cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper discusses the advancements in text generation using deep learning, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of AI and neural networks, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the diversification of generated content, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
